# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# polymbappe environment configuration — copy to `.env` and edit.
#
# POLYMBAPPE_* keys are loaded automatically by pydantic-settings.
# The third-party credentials further down (KAGGLE_*, REDDIT_*) are NOT read
# from .env automatically — export them into your shell before running the CLI:
#     set -a; . .env; set +a
# All values below are OPTIONAL; the core pipeline runs offline with none set.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- App settings (auto-loaded) --------------------------------------------
POLYMBAPPE_RANDOM_SEED=20260611
POLYMBAPPE_DATA_DIR=data
# Ollama model for the optional autotuner structural search (Phase 1).
# POLYMBAPPE_AUTOTUNE_LLM_MODEL=qwen3.5:9b

# --- Kaggle (player-attributes ingest, `[kaggle]` extra) -------------------
# Only needed for private/competition datasets or to lift anonymous rate
# limits; the default public dataset downloads without credentials. Get a token
# at kaggle.com -> Settings -> API -> Create New Token (or use ~/.kaggle/kaggle.json).
# KAGGLE_USERNAME=your_username
# KAGGLE_KEY=your_key

# --- Reddit (live agent news scan, `[context]` extra) ----------------------
# Read-only Reddit app credentials (no username/password needed). Only used when
# the agent's Reddit scan is enabled; without these it is skipped silently.
# Create an app at https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps (type: script).
# REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
# REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Not env vars — configured via files (see README "Opt-in input files"):
#   data/raw/polymarket_query.txt       Polymarket market slug filter
#   data/raw/player_attributes_kaggle.txt  Kaggle dataset slug for attributes
#   data/raw/football_data_urls.txt     Football-Data.co.uk odds CSV URLs
#   data/raw/squads_manifest.csv        Transfermarkt squad page mapping
#   data/raw/elo_url.txt                live published Elo (EloRatings.net)
# Ollama LLM (optional autotuner structural search) is a local server, not env:
#   ollama pull qwen2.5:7b
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
